    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation to authorial intent in its historical and canonical context. The movements below trace the chapter's theological argument from the covenant failure of verse 1 through the graduated mercy of verses 6-12 to the dual verdict of verses 13-14. The Chronicler writes not as a detached historian but as a theologian of covenant retribution and restoration, addressing a post-exilic community that needs both warning and hope.",
